node.text: I love this video.  This Airmen is exactly the type of Airmen you want to be friends with or have on your team.  His attitude and actions show no matter happens his future will be bright.  Why because he makes it bright.  I hope this energy spreads, a great Sunday vibe for the first day of August!  Big Salute to you A1C / Airman First Class,  Campise.

node.text: This is awesome!  Humboldt Bay, California crews, On June 19th, A 79 foot sailboat became disabled and the weather was getting bad.  Rescue swimmer and crew talk about a rescue this rescue.  First Rescue for the Rescue Swimmer.  Does the Coast Guard have a Talley of firsts like others in the USAF? First time you do something, you owe beer or that is how it used to be. #toml

node.title: Rescue Swimmer & Crew discuss a recent rescue!

node.text: Many ways to get to your  goals, this is a great example no matter what your goals are. Be realistic, I will never be a lead vocalist in a rock band no matter how hard I try.  Just not in the cards.  What's in the cards for you?  That's up to you for the most part and God given talent and drive.  God didn't want me to sing, that's all I can say🤣. This LT had a Business degree and wanted to be a pilot.  Air Force said no.  He joined as the enlisted ranks, and found another way.  Big Salute

node.text:
This is awesome & feel good video. A great Reenlistment Ceremony for Staff Sgt. Brenner, at Skydive Temple with Capt. Williams who provided Staff Sgt. Brenner the oath for his Army reenlistment, and accompanied him on skydive jump.

A huge thank you from First Army Division West was provided to local Veterans Scott Maschek, Federico Albacite, and Dena Donnell from Skydive Temple, and to Staff Sgt. Bermudezruelas and SSG Wiestling from 89th Military Police Brigade for  assisting for this the special occasion.

US Army photos and video footage by Master Sgt. Violet L. Dussault, Renention NCOIC, First Army Division West --thank you!

node.text: anding a CV-22 at a hospital needs to be validated.  We saw what happened when crews in the UK blew the landing surface apart at a local hospital.  Gryphon  Osx 21-1 was a recent training event to help validate this in Japan.  PJs (OR as PA called them Commando Medics) helped with this training event, by picking up the patient / process and package them.....for the hospital.  What are some of the things a PJ might do to package a patient prior to transload to the hospital?  #specialwarfareairmen

node.text: Ben Wilkinson, a professional big wave surfer and Patagonia ambassador from Oahu, Hawaii, tells about his experiences and provides his input regarding water and ocean safety. Wilkinson highlights the importance of being knowledgeable and prepared when planning to conduct water activities in any ocean across the globe. (U.S. Marine Corps video by Lance Cpl. Faith A. Rose and Cpl. Ryan H. Pulliam)

node.title: We all know someone lost to the sea.  Including combat dive qualified men

node.text: So much going on these last few weeks mostly humanitarian stuff, evacuations and lets not forget about the Earthquake in Haiti.  PJs and CCT deployed on this humanitarian mission to help the sick and wounded and keep the flow of aid coming in to the airfield quickly and efficiently.  God Bless all the folks in Haiti and the those helping them recover. Stay positive and keep that energy flowing to others. #specialwarfareairmen

node.text: Enlist on Race Day and with the USAF Special Warfare Truck, how cool is that.  For the first time, the NTT IndyCar Series shared the Indianapolis Motor Speedway’s road course with the NASCAR Cup Series in a race weekend doubleheader, Aug. 14-15, 2021, in Speedway, Indiana. The U.S. Air Force was represented in both races by Ed Carpenter Racing’s Conor Daly and Richard Petty Motorsports’ Erik Jones. Additionally, U.S. Maj. Gen. Matthew J. Burger, Air Force Reserve Command deputy commander, issued the oath of enlistment to 16 recruits. (U.S. Air Force video by Tech. Sgt. Ryan Conroy) #specialwarfareairmen

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Special Warfare Airmen on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
This multi day event looks brutal.  Everyone wants to be a sniper but do you think you could do it?  Talk about be able to be uncomfortable for long periods of time.  No whiners allowed.  These Bulgarian SOF are soaked, gassed, masked and tired but they drive on. "Ain't nothing but a thing"  Stay up, stay positive and have a great day.⁠
⁠

node.text: AATW!  Airborne All The Way, 16th of August is National Airborne day!  Odd news day for alot of people dealing with world events etc....Airborne Troops and some cadence should help get your mind right and hopefully spread some positive energy.  Happy Airborne day to all!

node.text: Who would like to fly in this beast?  It is massive....SOF troops were able to get some training during Northern Strike 2021!  It's Monday and alot going on in the world and a prayer goes out to our troops abroad working and friends who are having a rough time.  Haiti, Earthquake, Afghanistan and a few others.  Things in life always have cycles....this is just one of many.  Have a great Monday.
